Between Cornwallis island and some distant high land visible in the north, appeared a wide channel leading to the westward. A dark misty-looking cloud which hung over it, (technically termed “ frost-smoke'') was indicative of much open water in that direction.

This was the direction to which my instructionS, referring to the investigations at the National Observa· tory, concerning the winds and currents of the ocean, directed me to look for open water.

Nor was the open water the only indication that presented itself in confirmation of this theoretical con- jecture as to a milder climate in that direction.
